Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways. Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and fry for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{2%tsp} and @water for the curry{100%ml}.

Stir through the broccoli and bring to the boil, then cover with a lid and simmer until the broccoli is just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the broccoli is tender, remove the lid from the frying pan and stir through the @creme fraiche{150%g} until fully combined. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Once the sweet potato is roasted, stir it through the curry. Bring to the boil, then simmer on medium heat for ~{1-2%minutes}.

When ready, taste and season your curry with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #plates{}, then top with your korma style curry.

Enjoy!